headline: US stocks rise as gold hits another record and the dollar's value falls
summary: U.S. stocks are ticking higher Monday, while other markets make much louder moves, including another record-breaking rush for the price of gold.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 143 points, or 0.3%, as of 10 a.m. Eastern time, and the Nasdaq composite was 0.4% higher.  Baker Hughes helped lead the way and rose 3.6% after delivering a stronger profit for the latest quarter than analysts expected.
